CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1962, pg. 11, reads: "Setting Out Bush - Mrs. Inez Enty Simmons (on one knee) assists her husband, Herbert, in setting out a bush in Simmons' back yard, as Mrs. Laulie Bolden and Mrs Eula Reynolds looks on. The bush, a perennial, was a birthday gift from Mrs. Simmons to her husband."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Herbert Simmons, Inez Enty Simmons kneeling in garden planting bush, Laulie Bolden, and Eula Reynolds, gathered in garden in front of cinder block garage
